        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 28 at 3:16PM MST by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>Scattered snow showers will affect the central and southern
portions of Beaverhead County through 6 PM.

Some snow showers will reduce visibility below one half mile for a
short time. Additionally, wet roadways will gradually freeze over
this evening as colder air moves into the area. New snow
accumulations up to a half inch are possible from heavier snow
showers.

Those traveling across the central and southern portions of
Beaverhead County this afternoon should be alert for quickly
changing road conditions.
</description>
